You should not have *two* recursive calls per function execution context, but just one. Otherwise the number of recursive calls we be exponential O(2&lt;sup&gt;&#119899;&lt;/sup&gt;), while you only need O(n&#178;) calls of `bubbleSort`.

Use an `if` condition to decide which of the two recursive calls you need:

```
    if (j &lt; arr.length - 2) {
        bubbleSort(arr,index,j+1);
    } else {
        bubbleSort(arr,index+1,0);
    }
```

You can even make the condition a bit stricter, because in each phase of bubble sort, the sorted partition at the end of the array grows:

```
    if (j &lt; arr.length - 2 - index) {
```

You can also remove the stop condition on `j`.

